<br>
Seriously, this is what I do, but for me its a form of meditative escape...the story starts in a house...describe everything inside and outside the house to the smallest detail, by the time I am done trying to picture it, I am asleep....<br>
<br>
This doesnt work for my husband, he gets so wrapped up in the description, he wakes himself up trying to make everything perfect...for him, its a black space, free of sounds and color, he puts himself there and lets the darkness hold him..its safe (with no random thoughts) quiet (with no inner voices) and comfortable...so he falls asleep quickly...(I tried the black thing...something in the darkness growled at me, and I had to run to my comfy house to get away from it..<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
I try very hard to not use drugs to go to sleep ever...a cup of chamomile tea works well for me...OR..if I am REALLY haveing a hard time I will have a glass of wine and go read an old book....the wine relaxes me and the old book works because i dont have to anticipate whats going to happen, its well known and just takes me for a relaxing journey, not a roller coaster ride...(poetry books work well too)<br>
<br>
